reviews.text: A nice Italian restaurant with a great view. You can sit indoors or outdoors. Close to the harbor and the street is busy. Have a variety of alcoholic drinks. Pizza, pasta and all other Italian food is server there. Desserts too are served there. There are also non-alcoholic beverages. Food tastes good. The main course came with bread and different sauces. Tends to be on the expensive side.

Everything about this place is terrific, except the food, in my opinion. The location, views, and ambiance are spot on. The food was flavorless and the execution confusing. Green minestrone was a new one for me. Had the pasta with ground lamb. While it probably wasn't intentional, it tasted almost like an Asian/Italian fusion - lacking the flavor Italian should have. The home made pasta texture was good though.
The staff are super friendly. Great food, nice place and reasonable price ;)

We went there today for Easter Sunday brunch.  The space is very nice as it's big and bright; decor is pleasant for a mid-range restaurant.  The buffet was pretty extensive and pretty good; lots of quality hams, cheeses, salads, pizzas, meats, seafood.  I only gave it 3 stars as a) it wasn't cheap b) service was pretty poor c) the mains were horrible.
A fun Easter Event. Great food and staff. Manager went out of us way to help us with extra food fr the kids. Definitely recommend Spasso!
